aiResponses.unnamed_7: Application for Backend Engineer at GitLab. I am an experienced backend engineer with a proven track record building reliable, maintainable services and APIs; I am available for interviews on weekday mornings PT and can provide additional portfolio links on request.
aiResponses.question_33402666002:
I do not require any specific adjustments to participate fully in the standard interview process. I thrive in remote interview settings and have participated in multi-stage technical interviews, pairing sessions, and asynchronous coding exercises without any accommodations. If an adjustment were needed, I would request clear scheduling windows and the option to use screen-reader-friendly materials or extra time for timed coding tasks.

In prior backend roles I worked closely with hiring teams to ensure interviews were fair and accessible: I helped structure take-home exercises with clear acceptance criteria, documented APIs with examples and edge-case behaviors, and participated in mock interviews to surface and remove biases in technical evaluation. If selected, I am happy to work with your recruiting team to specify any accommodations in advance so that the interview experience is inclusive and effective for everyone.
